CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 13, 1961, pg. A14, reads: "Cutting Cake - Mr. and Mrs. James Orbison Jr. cut their elaborate wedding cake at the reception which followed their recent marriage. The bride is the former Marva Joan Tibbs. - Harris Photo."  Accompanying article reads: "Tibbs - Orbison Rites Held in Bride's Home - One of the season's prettiest brides is the former Marva Joan Tibbs, who became Mrs. James Orbison Jr. during a ceremony performed by Rev. J. C. Hairston at the home of the bride's parents, Mr. and Mrs. Otis Tibbs of Lowell St.  The groom is the son of Mr. and Mrs. James Orbison Sr. of Mayflower St.  A reception followed the rites.  The bride was attended by Audrey Wells, maid of honor, and Mary Orr, bridesmaid.  Frank Payne was best man and Edgar Benton an usher.  Among out-of-town guests attending the wedding were Mrs. Lila Nelson, Mr. and Mrs. Gardner Thomas of Scranton, Pa.; Mr. and Mrs. Harvey Nelson, Harrisburg; Mrs. Marsha Hogan, Cleveland, and Mr. and Mrs. Abe Washington of Philadelphia.  The bride was feted at a shower given by Mrs. Janice Jackson, 636[?] Lowell St., prior to the wedding."
TitMainTitle: Groom James Orbison Jr., and bride Marva Joan Tibbs Orbison wearing gown with lace sleeves, cutting four tiered wedding cake, in Tibbs home on Lowell Street, another version
